observations.recommendation:
We recommended that Management require:
The creation of an inventory committee consisting of representatives from different concerned offices to conduct an inventory of the local roads under the jurisdiction of the LGU who will prepare the necessary Report on the Physical Count of the Road Network System (RPCRNS) using the form in Annex C of COA Circular 2015-008. The RPCRNS should be reconciled with the Accounting and GSO records;
The Municipal Engineer to provide the Accountant and the General Services Officer with the complete description and segregation of road components for those with data on construction costs. For those not posted in the registry but without identified cost and those included in the RPCRNS but not in the registry, the fair value must be used in determining the cost of road components and thereafter shall provide the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects;
The Municipal Accountant to (1) prepare and maintain Local Road Network Ledger Cards for the road and its components, (2) disclose in the Notes to Financial Statements the Road Network System and (3) depreciate the carrying amount of existing roads and its components to reflect the asset in its used condition and accordingly adjust the amount recorded in the Road Network account supported by the RPCRNS, Registry Infrastructure for Roads and working paper on the determination of the depreciated replacement cost per registry. Subsequently, at the end of each year, a lapsing schedule for the computation of depreciation for each depreciable road component must be prepared as basis for recording depreciation expenses and the required Local Road Network Ledger Card for each road network shall likewise be maintained; and
The Municipal General Services Office at the end or every accounting period to render a Report on Local Road Network using the pro-forma schedule in Annex A of same Circular and maintain local road inventory, Road Map and complete Road Network Property Card for all roads and its components.

To ensure fair presentation of the financial statements and compliance with accounting standards and regulations, we recommended that the Municipal Accountant:
Conduct a thorough reconciliation of the Due from Other Funds and Due to Other Funds accounts to determine the cause of the discrepancy and make necessary adjustments to ensure that both accounts are properly recognized;
Prepare the necessary adjusting entries to correct the account balances;
Maintain subsidiary ledgers as necessary and include disclosure in the Notes to Financial Statements for transparency; and
Strengthen internal controls and monitoring mechanisms to prevent future discrepancies in reciprocal accounts.

We recommended that Management:
Strictly comply with the mandated 20% appropriation requirement under Section 287 of R.A. No. 7160 to avoid appropriation deficits;
Promote equitable sectoral distribution of the 20% Development Fund by enhancing implementation of Social and Environmental Services Projects;
Strengthen planning, programming and procurement processes to ensure that all projects under the 20% Development Fund are well-planned and procurement-and-implementation-ready, in accordance with Item 3.2 of DBM-DOF-DILG JMC No. 1, s. 2020;
Reassess the viability of various PPAs which have remained unimplemented for 2-10 years. If deemed impractical or non-priority, consider realignment or reprogramming of these funds for other eligible projects;
Revisit the Local Development Plan and Annual Investment Program to ensure equitable allocation across social, economic, and environmental sectors; and
Submit updated status reports (physical and financial) on all Continuing Appropriations.

We recommended that Management:
Develop and enforce an internal memorandum or directive requiring all concerned personnel to submit the Acceptance and Inspection Reports (AIRs) within 24 hours of goods acceptance;
Implement a tracking system for AIR submission;
Assign a focal person responsible for consolidating and submitting AIRs to the Office of the Auditor within the prescribed timeframe; and
If necessary, conduct a re-orientation for General Services Office personnel and end-users regarding proper documentation and timely submission of AIRs in accordance with COA Circulars.

We recommended that Management instruct the:
Immediate supervisor or head of office to certify that services were rendered before processing the payroll;
Municipal Treasurer to certify fund availability before payroll disbursement;
Municipal Accountant to certify completeness and propriety of supporting documents and the liquidation of previous cash advances or the existence of funds held in trust, if applicable; and
Disbursing Officer to affix his or her certification of payment for all payroll disbursements.

The Municipal Accountant to prepare and maintain Local Road Network Ledger Cards for the road and its components namely: (1) road lot, (2) road pavement, (3) drainage and slope protection structures and (4) other miscellaneous structure.  Further, prepare a lapsing schedule for the computation of depreciation of each road component, and disclose the Road Network System in the Notes to Financial Statements;

The Municipal GSO to (1.) Prepare and submit the Report on the Physical Count of Local Road Network, (2.) Maintain a complete Local Road Network Property Card for all roads and its components, and (3.) Maintain a Local Road Inventory and Road Map; and

The Municipal Accountant and the Municipal GSO to secure from the Municipal Engineer the complete description and cost segregation of road components of every road project undertaken for them to have a basis in recording the road networks in the Local Road Network Ledger Card and Local Road Network Property Card, respectively.

We recommended that Management require the Municipal Accountant:

To reconcile with the Municipal Treasurer the Cash accounts records on a quarterly basis to reflect an accurate and reliable balance at any particular period;

To create an effective and efficient internal control system to avoid future negative balances of Cash in Bank - account as prescribed by Section 58 of PD 1445, and to present accurate and reliable reports that are useful and not misleading to its users.

